    "description": "An exciting career opportunity awaits you at Symbiosis Hospital. We are on the lookout for a dedicated Surgeon to strengthen our Jabalpur-based team.\n\nAbout Symbiosis Hospital:\nSymbiosis Hospital is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Coordinate with multidisciplinary teams for comprehensive patient management\n• Educate patients and families on health management and disease prevention\n• Participate in quality improvement initiatives and clinical audits\n• Ensure patient privacy and maintain confidentiality\n• Maintain sterile environments and follow infection control protocols\n• Conduct routine health assessments and screenings\n• Collaborate with pharmaceutical representatives and medical suppliers\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Sc / M.Sc in Life Sciences\n• 6-10 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in ICU Management\n• Proficiency in EMR/EHR\n• Proficiency in Clinical Documentation\n• Proficiency in CPT Codes\n• Proficiency in HIPAA Compliance\n• Proficiency in Medical Ethics\n• Proficiency in Diagnostic Skills\n• Proficiency in Medical Coding\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Company-sponsored certifications\n• Maternity and paternity leave\n• Meal coupons and food allowance\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Mobile and internet reimbursement\n• Salary Range: 12 LPA - 25 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Jabalpur, Madhya Pradesh, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Symbiosis Hospital!",
